INSERT INTO `caching` (`page_id`,`content`,`touched`) VALUES (59,'<h1 class=\"wiki_title\">Compact Set</h1><div class=\"ui segment compact wiki_toc\"><ol class=\"\"><li id=\"rh_0\">0 <a  href=\"#h_0\">Definition</a></li><li id=\"rh_1\">1 <a  href=\"#h_1\">Criterion</a></li><li id=\"rh_2\">2 <a  href=\"#h_2\">Properties</a><ol class=\"\"><li id=\"rh_2_0\">2.0 <a  href=\"#h_2_0\">General</a></li><li id=\"rh_2_1\">2.1 <a  href=\"#h_2_1\">In metric space X</a></li></ol></li></ol></div><p>ì˜¹ê³¨ ì§‘í•©</p><h1 class=\"ui dividing header\" id=\"h_0\"><a href=\"#rh_0\">0</a> Definition</h1><p>A subset K of a <a class=\"wiki_nonexisting_page\" href=\"/wiki/view/Topology\" title=\"topological space\">topological space</a> X is called compact set if every open cover of K contains a finite subcover.</p><h1 class=\"ui dividing header\" id=\"h_1\"><a href=\"#rh_1\">1</a> Criterion</h1><div class=\"wiki_list\"><ul class = \"ui list\"><li>In Euclidean space, closed and bounded set is compact.</li></ul></div><h1 class=\"ui dividing header\" id=\"h_2\"><a href=\"#rh_2\">2</a> Properties</h1><h2 class=\"ui dividing header\" id=\"h_2_0\"><a href=\"#rh_2_0\">2.0</a> General</h2><div class=\"wiki_list\"><ul class = \"ui list\"><li>Compactness is a property of the set it self in some way, which means: <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi><mo>âŠ‚</mo><mi>Y</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X \\subset Y</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;\"></span><span class=\"strut bottom\" style=\"height:0.72243em;vertical-align:-0.0391em;\"></span><span class=\"base textstyle uncramped\"><span class=\"mord mathit\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"mrel\">âŠ‚</span><span class=\"mord mathit\" style=\"margin-right:0.22222em;\">Y</span></span></span></span>, Y is a topological space, X is topological subspace of Y. Then if K is compact relative to X, also relative to Y, vice versa.</li><li>Closed subset of a compact set is compact.</li><li>Infinite subset of K has a limit point in K.</li></ul></div><h2 class=\"ui dividing header\" id=\"h_2_1\"><a href=\"#rh_2_1\">2.1</a> In <a class=\"wiki_nonexisting_page\" href=\"/wiki/view/metric space\" title=\"metric space\">metric space</a> X</h2><div class=\"wiki_list\"><ul class = \"ui list\"><li>Compact set is closed.<sup id=\"rfn_0\"><a href=\"#fn_0\">[0]</a></sup></li><li>Intersection of a closed set with K is also compact.</li><li> If <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math><semantics><mrow><mo>{</mo><msub><mi>K</mi><mi>Î±</mi></msub><mo>}</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\"> \\{ K_\\alpha\\} </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.75em;\"></span><span class=\"strut bottom\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"base textstyle uncramped\"><span class=\"mopen\">{</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathit\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">K</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist\"><span style=\"top:0.15em;margin-right:0.05em;margin-left:-0.07153em;\"><span class=\"fontsize-ensurer reset-size5 size5\"><span style=\"font-size:0em;\">â€‹</span></span><span class=\"reset-textstyle scriptstyle cramped mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathit mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.0037em;\">Î±</span></span></span><span class=\"baseline-fix\"><span class=\"fontsize-ensurer reset-size5 size5\"><span style=\"font-size:0em;\">â€‹</span></span>â€‹</span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose\">}</span></span></span></span> is a collection of compact subsets of a metric space X such that the intersection of every finite subcollection is nonempty, then <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math><semantics><mrow><mo>âˆ©</mo><msub><mi>K</mi><mi>Î±</mi></msub><mo>â‰ </mo><mi mathva