INSERT INTO `caching` (`page_id`,`content`,`touched`) VALUES (149,'<h1 class=\"wiki_title\">How our brain group words by meaning</h1><div class=\"ui segment compact wiki_toc\"><ol class=\"\"><li id=\"rh_0\">0 <a  href=\"#h_0\">See Also</a></li><li id=\"rh_1\">1 <a  href=\"#h_1\">Bibliography</a></li></ol></div><p>When our brain store the words, we group words by its meaning. Researchers found that same category of words is processed in same region of our brain and the location of the category is same for each person. For example, same region of brain is activated when we hear some word about color like red, purple, etc.</p><p>You can also explore brain map in <a class=\"wiki_ext_link\" href=\"http://gallantlab.org/huth2016/\" title=\"here\">here<i class=\"external square icon\"></i></a>.</p><h1 class=\"ui dividing header\" id=\"h_0\"><a href=\"#rh_0\">0</a> See Also</h1><div class=\"wiki_list\"><ul class = \"ui list\"><li><a class=\"wiki_ext_link\" href=\"http://www.nature.com/nature/journal/v532/n7600/full/nature17637.html\" title=\"Huth, Alexander G., et al. \"Natural speech reveals the semantic maps that tile human cerebral cortex.\" Nature 532.7600 (2016): 453-458.\">Huth, Alexander G., et al. \"Natural speech reveals the semantic maps that tile human cerebral cortex.\" Nature 532.7600 (2016): 453-458.<i class=\"external square icon\"></i></a></li><li><a class=\"wiki_ext_link\" href=\"http://gallantlab.org/huth2016/\" title=\"Brain Map\">Brain Map<i class=\"external square icon\"></i></a></li></ul></div><h1 class=\"ui dividing header\" id=\"h_1\"><a href=\"#rh_1\">1</a> Bibliography</h1><div class=\"wiki_list\"><ul class = \"ui list\"><li>https://aeon.co/videos/see-how-our-brains-group-words-by-meaning-in-surprisingly-complex-semantic-maps</li></ul></div><p><div class=\"ui negative message\"><div class=\"header\">Macro Error</div><p>Macro tag>aeon, doesn\'t supported.</p></div></p>','2017-12-31 23:54:42.000');
